# Source Authority (Internal)

## Hard rules

1. Do **not** add user-visible menus, screens, banners, or settings for source priority.
2. Do **not** advertise this policy to end users.
3. Korea-related fact search / verification / grounding in **Korean Context Engine, Writing, Translator, Research, Chat** (internal pipelines only) must prefer official primary sources.
4. President / Presidential Office / speeches / briefings / schedules / national vision / national agenda → **https://www.president.go.kr/** first.
5. Law, statistics, judgments, elections, finance → the **direct official agency** for that domain first.
6. Use existing citation UI only when the feature already shows sources — do not invent new citation chrome.
7. Do **not** full-crawl or bulk-mirror official sites; fetch claim-specific materials only.
8. Canonical doc: `docs/SOURCE_AUTHORITY.md`. Constants: `class-yoy-source-authority.php` (no UI wiring unless a later Phase explicitly ships Source Authority Layer).

## When translating

Ordinary phrase translation does not need presidential portal fetches. Apply this policy when the pipeline asserts or verifies **Korea-specific official facts**.
